column18: 09/17/1999: Unknown assailants threw a petrol bomb at the Austrian Embassy in Copenhagen, Denmark. There were no casualties and only minor fire damage to the building occurred.
column125: Officials questioned whether this attack was connected to the murder of Red Army Faction (RAF) member Horst Ludwig Meyer, which occurred several days earlier.
